comment.narrative:
The project will be aligned to the main development policy guidelines set out in the ‘Sector Strategies for Livestock Production, Feed and Pastoral Production’ document and will be implemented at the national level. For more specific, value chain-related activities, the project will be implemented within the governorate of Béja. The governorate of Béja is situated in the north-west of Tunisia, covers an area of 374,000 ha and has a population of 304,000 inhabitants. This area has the greatest potential for developing milk production in Tunisia and also has:
- 12,000 dairy farmers, around 85% of whom are smallholders with fewer than five cows;
- 45,000 dairy cows, 18,000 of which are purebred cattle (40%);
- Annual milk production of 115 million litres (2013 figures);
- 23 milk collection centres with a daily capacity of around 150,000 litres. These centres collect 65 million litres a year (2012 figures) or 56% of all the milk produced.

